<br>
Some stats are meaningful.  Some stats are less meaningful.  Some stats are irrelevant.  ALL relevant stats have points of diminishing returns (or outright caps) that are relative to the situation.<br>
<br>
Testing and experience tell you when you have reached these points.  Trying different set ups tells you more about the relative value of each item.<br>
<br>
All that said, for me (my gear and most situations I fight in) I would find 10 raw attack 30hp 6ac and 2/tick regen to be more valuable than 13ac 65 hp and the saves on the second belt.  The decision is easy for me because in most cases I am ac capped, have sufficient hp, and good saves.  If I were a 3200hp 1085ac warrior with 54DR and was planning on tanking Zlandicar... then I might want the second belt <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
My point is this: do some testing, do some thinking, ask other people you respect about how they select their gear.  Understanding the real tradeoffs helps you make much better decisions across a wider variety of situations than dogmatic adherence to some silly equations.<br>
<br>
